quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,22,"You are not a dictator over them -"
  88,23,"Save the one who turns away and disbelieves.{1}",footnotes:1:{88:23} See footnote of {8:39}.
  88,24,"Then Allâh will punish him with the greatest punishment."
  89,19,"And you devour the inheritance all with greed."
  89,20,"And you love wealth with much love."
  89,21,"Nay! When the earth is ground to powder."
  90,13,"(It is) freeing a neck (slave){1}",footnotes:1:{90:13} Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: "Whoever frees a Muslim slave, Allâh will save all the parts of his body from the (Hell) Fire, as he has freed the body-parts of the slave." (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.3, Hadith No.693).
  90,14,"Or giving food in a day of hunger (famine),"
  90,15,"To an orphan near of kin."
  91,10,"And indeed he fails who corrupts his ownself (i.e. disobeys what Allâh has ordered by rejecting the true Faith of Islâmic Monotheism or by following polytheism or by doing every kind of evil wicked deeds)."
  91,11,"Thamûd (people) denied (their Prophet) through their transgression (by rejecting the true Faith of Islâmic Monotheism, and by following polytheism, and by committing every kind of sin)."
  91,12,"When the most wicked man among them went forth (to kill the she-camel)."
  92,7,"We will make smooth for him the path of ease (goodness)."
  92,8,"But he who is greedy miser and thinks himself self-sufficient.{1}",footnotes:1:{92:8} Narrated ‘Alî رضي الله عنه : We were in the company of the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم and he said, "There is none among you but has his place written for him, either in Paradise or in the Hell-fire." We said, "O Allâh’s Messenger! Shall we depend (on this fact and give up work)?" He replied, "No! Carry on doing good deeds, for everybody will find easy (to do) such deeds as will lead him to his destined place." Then the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم recited: "As for him who gives (in charity) and keeps his duty to Allâh and fears Him, and believes in Al-Husnâ. We will make smooth for him the path of ease..." (V.92:5-10) (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.6, Hadith No.472).
  92,9,"And belies Al-Husnâ (See the footnote of the Verse No.6)"
  93,4,"And indeed the Hereafter is better for you than the present (life of this world)."
  93,5,"And verily, your Lord will give you (all good) so that you shall be well-pleased."
  93,6,"Did He not find you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) an orphan and gave you a refuge?"
  94,1,"Have We not opened your breast for you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)?"
  94,2,"And removed from you your burden."
  94,3,"Which weighed down your back?"